{
  "_description": "TTS pronunciation dictionary. Each entry: 'pattern' (whole word to match), plus backend-specific keys ('pocket', 'kokoro', etc.) or 'replacement' as universal fallback. 'ipa' is reference only. Backend-specific key wins over 'replacement'. Matching is whole-word, case-sensitive by default. Set 'case_sensitive': false for case-insensitive.",
  "_known_bugs": [
    "pocket-tts ghost/whisper noise: confirmed triggers include 'awth' and 'oh auth'. May only occur in table context (short isolated cells) — same words in flowing sentences seem fine. Root cause unclear: could be 'awth', 'oh' before certain phonemes, table chunking, or a combo. The dictionary uses 'o-auth' (no h) which avoids it. Workaround: vary vowel spelling in replacements. Reproduced on Windows with pocket voice clone (both old voice and DWP). May be worth filing upstream."
  ],
